#: ../../C/COME-FROM.rst:5
msgid "COME FROM"
msgstr "COME FROM"

#: ../../C/COME-FROM.rst:7
msgid "n\\."
msgstr "名詞"

#: ../../C/COME-FROM.rst:9
msgid ""
"A semi-mythical language construct dual to the ‘go to’; :code:`COME FROM` "
"<label> would cause the referenced label to act as a sort of trapdoor, so "
"that if the program ever reached it control would quietly and "
":ref:`automagically` be transferred to the statement following the "
":code:`COME FROM`\\. :code:`COME FROM` was first proposed in R. Lawrence "
"Clark's *A Linguistic Contribution to GOTO-less programming*\\, which "
"appeared in a 1973 :ref:`Datamation` issue (and was reprinted in the April "
"1984 issue of *Communications of the ACM*\\). This parodied the then-raging "
"‘structured programming’ :ref:`holy-wars` (see :ref:`considered-harmful`\\)."
" Mythically, some variants are the assigned COME FROM and the computed COME "
"FROM (parodying some nasty control constructs in FORTRAN and some extended "
"BASICs). Of course, multi-tasking (or non-determinism) could be implemented "
"by having more than one :code:`COME FROM` statement coming from the same "
"label."
msgstr ""
"‘go to’と双対をなす、半ば神話的な言語構文。\\ :code:`COME FROM`\\ "
"<label>は、参照されたラベルを一種の落とし戸のように振る舞わせます。つまり、プログラムがそのラベルに到達すると、制御は静かに\\ "
":ref:`automagically`\\ に\\ :code:`COME FROM`\\ の次の文へ転送されます。\\ :code:`COME "
"FROM`\\ は、1973年の\\ :ref:`Datamation`\\ 誌に掲載された(そして1984年4月号の『Communications "
"of the ACM』に再録された)R. Lawrence Clarkの『A Linguistic Contribution to GOTO-less "
"programming』で初めて提案されました。これは当時激しく繰り広げられていた‘構造化プログラミング’の\\ :ref:`holy-wars`\\ "
"をパロディ化したものでした(\\ :ref:`considered-harmful`\\ を参照)。神話的には、いくつかの変種として代入COME "
"FROMや計算COME "
"FROMがあります(FORTRANのいくつかの厄介な制御構文や一部の拡張BASICをパロディ化したものです)。もちろん、同じラベルから来る\\ "
":code:`COME FROM`\\ 文を複数持つことで、マルチタスク(または非決定性)を実装することもできるでしょう。"

#: ../../C/COME-FROM.rst:15
msgid ""
"In some ways the FORTRAN :code:`DO` looks like a :code:`COME FROM` "
"statement. After the terminating statement number/:code:`CONTINUE` is "
"reached, control continues at the statement following the DO. Some generous "
"FORTRANs would allow arbitrary statements (other than :code:`CONTINUE`\\) "
"for the statement, leading to examples like:"
msgstr ""
"ある意味でFORTRANの\\ :code:`DO`\\ は\\ :code:`COME FROM`\\ 文のように見えます。終端の文番号/\\ "
":code:`CONTINUE`\\ に到達した後、制御はDOの次の文から続きます。一部の寛大なFORTRANはその文に(\\ "
":code:`CONTINUE`\\ 以外の)任意の文を許したため、次のような例につながりました。"

#: ../../C/COME-FROM.rst:28
msgid ""
"in which the trapdoor is just after the statement labeled 10. (This is "
"particularly surprising because the label doesn't appear to have anything to"
" do with the flow of control at all!) While sufficiently astonishing to the "
"unsuspecting reader, this form of :code:`COME FROM` statement isn't "
"completely general. After all, control will eventually pass to the following"
" statement. The implementation of the general form was left to Univac "
"FORTRAN, ca. 1975 (though a roughly similar feature existed on the IBM 7040 "
"ten years earlier). The statement :code:`AT 100` would perform a :code:`COME"
" FROM 100`\\. It was intended strictly as a debugging aid, with dire "
"consequences promised to anyone so deranged as to use it in production code."
" More horrible things had already been perpetrated in production languages, "
"however; doubters need only contemplate the :code:`ALTER` verb in "
":ref:`COBOL`\\. :code:`COME FROM` was supported under its own name for the "
"first time 15 years later, in C-INTERCAL (see :ref:`INTERCAL`\\, "
":ref:`retrocomputing`\\); knowledgeable observers are still reeling from the"
" shock."
msgstr ""
"ここで落とし戸はラベル10の付いた文の直後にあります。(ラベルが制御の流れとはまったく関係がないように見えるため、これは特に驚くべきことです!) "
"油断している読者には十分驚きですが、この形の\\ :code:`COME FROM`\\ "
"文は完全に一般的というわけではありません。結局のところ、制御はいずれ次の文に渡されるのです。一般形の実装は1975年頃のUnivac "
"FORTRANに委ねられました(ただし10年前のIBM 7040にもほぼ同様の機能が存在していました)。\\ :code:`AT 100`\\ "
"という文は\\ :code:`COME FROM 100`\\ "
"を実行します。それは厳密にデバッグ補助として意図され、それを本番コードで使うほど錯乱した者には恐ろしい結果が約束されていました。しかしながら、本番用言語ではすでにもっとひどいことが行われていました。疑う者は\\"
" :ref:`COBOL`\\ の\\ :code:`ALTER`\\ 動詞を考えてみればよいのです。\\ :code:`COME FROM`\\ "
"がその名前のもとで初めてサポートされたのはその15年後、C-INTERCALにおいてでした(\\ :ref:`INTERCAL`\\ 、\\ "
":ref:`retrocomputing`\\ を参照)。事情に詳しい観察者たちは今なおその衝撃から立ち直れずにいます。"
